notes: |
  Final temp: 56°C on average (try setting predictive thermo to 50°C, 54 seems overcooked)
components:
  - name: pan only (thin steaks, < 1")
    steps:
      - heat pan to 200°C
      - cook until visible from the side
      - flip, cook roughly the same again
  - name: reverse-sear (thicker steaks, > 1")
    steps:
      - (Optional) dry brine with salt 1-5 hours ahead of time and leave in fridge
      - Preheat oven to 150°C (to reduce time, lower is fine if you have more time; Claude says 120°C max)
      - Cook in oven until surface temp reaches near final temp
      - optionally leave in freezer for 5 mins to chill surface
      - Drop oven/grill temp to 80°C and continue cooking
      - When surface temp starts to rise, lower oven temp to 5°C above target temp (i.e. 60°C)
      - Rest in fridge for up to 30 mins to cool the crust region (minimises grey line)
      - Heat pan to 240°C
      - Sear steak in hot pan to get crust
      - Turn regularly, 30s per-side (grey line bad)
      - (Optional) Finish with butter, tallow, and/or lemon
  - name: regular sear
    steps:
      - Heat pan to 200°C (maybe too hot, tbd)
      - Heat oven to 125°C
      - Sear both sides, 30s per side at a time, keep turning til happy
      - 'Once good crust, put in oven until internal temp reaches 48°C (TODO: confirm)'
      - (Optional) sear again at the end for heat and final crust
  - name: t-bone
    steps:
      - cook sirloin side more than fillet side
      - sear fat cap and both faces
      - oven until sirloin at 40°C, fillet at 36°C
      - rest until sirloin at 52°C, fillet at 48°C
      - final sear again
